SIMPLE: skim
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skim
<hw>Skim</hw> <pr>(sk⟦icr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Skimmed</conjf> <pr>(sk⟦icr⟧md)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Skimming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>skymma</ets> to darken. ⟦root⟧158. See <er>Scum</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To clear (a liquid) from scum or substance floating or
lying thereon, by means of a utensil that passes just beneath the
surface; <as>as, to <ex>skim</ex> milk; to <ex>skim</ex>
broth.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take off by skimming; <as>as, to <ex>skim</ex>
cream</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To pass near the surface of; to brush the surface
of; to glide swiftly along the surface of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Homer describes Mercury as flinging himself from the top of
Olympus, and <qex>skimming</qex> the surface of the ocean.</q>
<rj><qau>Hazlitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Fig.: To read or examine superficially and rapidly,
in order to cull the principal facts or thoughts; <as>as, to
<ex>skim</ex> a book or a newspaper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skim</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skim
<hw>Skim</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pass lightly; to
glide along in an even, smooth course; to glide along near the
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not so when swift Camilla scours the plain,⟦br⟧
Flies o'er the unbending corn, and <qex>skims</qex> along the main.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To hasten along with superficial
attention.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>skim</qex> over a science in a very superficial
survey.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To put on the finishing coat of plaster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skim</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Skim
<hw>Skim</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Contraction of <er>Skimming</er> and
<er>Skimmed</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Skim coat</b></col>, <cd>the final or finishing coat of
plaster.</cd> -- <col><b>Skim colter</b></col>, <cd>a colter for paring
off the surface of land.</cd> -- <col><b>Skim milk</b></col>,
<cd>skimmed milk; milk from which the cream has been
taken.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Srim</ent>⟦br⟧
